data.body: Southern-Thai Muslim restaurant.

reviews.text: Food took too long...

There are 5 of us. We ordered the couple set of chicken & beef. Food spread was superb. Tomyam was super nice. We finished all food except for the green curry which is not to our liking. Overall we cleared all dishes!!!

Have known Koh Nangkam since 2013 and the first time I had dinner with my family in the aforementioned year, everything was perfect. From the food to the dining experience and even the customer service.

I made a trip here again in October 2021 and the service fell short of my expectation. For starters, you will have to choose what you wish to order before you enter their restaurant and they will take forever to serve you one of the dishes that you have ordered. That's fine, I guess there must have been a slight mix-up or the chef overlooked on our order since every other dish arrived on time.

Today, I paid a visit there and the service was appalling. For someone who placed a reservation at 2 and arrived there on time, we were only served with our food at 2:40pm. The tom yum soup that we ordered was cold by the time the waiter served us our dishes and the bell that's on the table to ring the waiter to enquire about your order? Don't bother pressing that because no one will approach you, especially when you are seated on the second floor. I came here, hoping my friend would be impressed with the food, ambience, and the service, but safe to say, she wasn't the least impressed after our meal.

When it's time to pay at the counter, even the person at the counter would take 10-15 minutes to serve you (even when there's no queue). I am extremely disappointed with the service rendered by the wait staff and definitely won't be returning again.

The two stars are only for the cost of the dishes we both ordered. Nothing else.
Best Thai food. Taste so original like I had in Krabi.
Nice food, cozy ambience. A good place for family. The food was good. Very nice indeed. We finished practically everything we ordered. Oh.. we ordered the set for 4 pax. 😉

data.body: Ignite your senses with an Arabesque feast at La Fez. Try their almond tart - a fruity, nutty and creamy all rolled into one, topped with Chantilly cream and fresh figs.

reviews.text: Excellent food and good service. They have a good selection of Moroccan dishes and drinks. Must try are the assorted dips with pita bread, Mandi rice with chicken and not to miss are their lip smacking desserts! Tried the chocolate caramel banana mousse and will recommend as a top highlight of the place. Will definitely visit the place again. Great work done by the La Fez team.
Great food. Though it’s priced on the higher end, the food taste and quality makes up for it. The ambience is also great along with great customer service experience. Will def go again

A quiet place to have a late lunch. A lady service staff was manning the place and was attentive despite having to multitask. A simple pita and lamb dish was almost $30, a typical price for exotic cuisine, but unfortunately, doesn't deliver value, as there wasn't a wow factor. I'd say its an IG worthy place and you pay the premium for it.

Food was excellent, interior was really pretty as well. The manager was really friendly, and served us well - however the service by the staff can be improved. We had to keep reminding them on the food/ drinks/ utensils we had asked for. Other than that, really enjoyed the food!

If u love pink this cafe is for u.

Price on the higher side. Food is good. Dip is very good. Take great pictures

If u have kids, LOOK AWAY, no kids friendly meal, more importantly not a toddler friendly environment. Fragile display items at toddler height

Smelly toilet

data.body: Located on level 2 of The Straits Teppanyaki, Rumi The Poets Cup is best known for their artisanal drinks accompanied by poetry notes for an added touch. Quench your thirst with Rumi's masterfully crafted Artisanal Coffee and mocktail selection. They have been a local favourite for years.

reviews.text: Great ambience. Great people! Had gone for a birthday dinner here, the steak is tender and price is affordable! Bonus points are the cashback we received at the end of the visit. Will definitely come back again.

Ambience was simple, however the steak was succulent and tender. Prawns were fresh and Extra Large. Must try the desserts, simply delicious and generous portion. The waitress, Huda was very cheerful, helpful and warm. She was very warm, friendly and patient.

My first visit here today with my family. We were looking forward to having a great meal but we were extremely disappointed with the quality of the food. The squid was slightly undercooked. When i asked about the squid, he told me that the feedback from other customers that the squid is chewy if overcooked,  therefore they undercooked the squid but it came with the hot plate that was at room temperature! It could not continue cooking my undercooked squid! All the side dishes were not even warm! Definitely overpriced! If i could give 0 stars, i would! I dont understand what the hype was all about. I am sure to say that today will be my first and my last visit here. Definitely not recommended!!!

It was the first time after a very long time that my siblings and I got together. We had our lunch here and we were blown away by everything. The dining experience here got us speechless. We rushed to take some photos of the food (missed out on a few) and then we quickly dig in. The staffs were friendly and hospitable, the restaurant had a cosy atmosphere and serves delicious food. If only we had bigger appetite to order and eat more 😂

Thank you Straits Teppanyaki ❤️
One of my best dinners. The wagyu is very soft and all of the food portions are just right. The drinks.. fabulous. 🥰 overall ambience is amazing.

data.body: Boba fans, get a taste of Singapore with Milk's Ice Kacang Bubble Tea. They also offer crispy, fluffy honeycomb Waffles – a delightful dessert for any sweet-tooth.

reviews.text: Went there for strawberry milk and caramel milk tea. Something new, you can create your own drink by choose either milk/milk tea and topping or they have their own drink flavour too. Don't worry if you not sure how to do it, there is instructions or just ask the staff. Friendly and good service. I saw this from tiktok so I decided to try. Recommended.

The staff at the outlet is nice and pleasant. She was attentive and had kindly explain the menu and concept to us.

I ordered directly off the menu a Brown Sugar Milk Brulee without ice (additional $1). It does have the taste and fragrant of the brown sugar. However, I find it too sweet.
Only one person working. Taking order and making drinks. But he calmly get the work done!👍🏻
Rebranded @milk.singapore outlet! Loving the hands on experience. Their Taro milk tea with pearl and ovaltine milk tea with ice cream is 😍💕👍💯💯💯

tried two drinks, matcha mascarpone and grape cream cheese. both were disappointing - grape cream cheese was way, way too sweet and only had a bit of cream cheese while the pearls in the matcha mascarpone were not cooked well and barely had a touch of cream cheese. i understand the pricing for the ice blended grape drink ($6) but the matcha mascarpone ($6.80) is way too expensive for what you get - a subpar matcha latte with badly cooked pearls and a bit of cheese. we couldn’t finish either of the drinks and had to toss them out 😩

data.body: Some say they have one of the best Halal Buttermilk Waffles in town. Pair it with one of their signature gelato and you might rethink sharing this dessert.

reviews.text: Great waffles! Crispy outside and moist inside. Nicely balanced with the maple syrup. Eat by itself and have the ice cream separate. I recommend the Salted Peanut Butter.
Great ambience. Fluffy waffles and great choice of ice cream. The savoury menu is impressive as well. Not overprice, just nice. Highly recommended.
One of the best waffle I've had in a long time. I got the waffle with peanut butter ice-cream. Pair it with their latte and it's to die for. Highly recommend.

The waitress was really pleasant and polite (not all cafes have friendly staff nowadays).
The overall vibe was very chill. The waffles and ice cream definitely blew me over as it was so flavourful and creamy. The waffles were toasty crisp perfection was excellent paired with the drizzled maple syrup. Very yummy and can't wait to be back!

Waffles here were fantastic! One of the best I've had. Crisp on the outside and airy and fluffy on the inside with just the right amount of bite to it. Was also really tasty w/o being too sweet.

The dark chocolate ice cream was amazing too, can really taste the quality there. Ondeh ondeh flavour lacked some creaminess but overall still very satisfied. Well done!

data.body: Indian-Muslim restaurant known for their nasi biryani and murtabak.

reviews.text: Good clean kitchen and toilet. Food taste nice and price is reasonable. Friendly staff.

This restaurant is in a great location as well as infront of a mosque. To enjoy your food much better they have an air-conditioning room above to sit down and relax. Lots of options on their menu card and their staffs are super polite. Absolutely loved the food (it's spicy for people who ain't used to spices food).
The best murtabak in town. Very generous fillings interlaced with eggs. Spicy and delicious curry too.

First time at the restaurant after passing by it a few times. Totally regretted my decision this morming. I was served by a rude staff (tall, male, with a scrawny beard) who told me off for my queries. I had asked about the price of the lamb shank (its $25 or thereabouts) and if they sell mutton korma.
He gave me a condescending look and said korma is same as curry. And when I asked if they had murtabak ready to go (coz I saw them making a bunch at the back) he let go a tirade of verbal abuse and accused me of being able to buy from Islamic Restaurant which is more expensive but had so many questions at his shop (I asked 3 questions to help me make a decision on what to buy). I was shocked and was speechless for a second. I then regained my composure and replied that it's my first time and there was no price list so I had to make enquiries. I was buying the briyani fr Islamic for some one and I didn't have to explain to him anything. I admonished him for being so rude towards me and for his insulting remarks and said that he has lost a customer. He said ok. I then turned to his colleague and informed him that this guy is so rude to me and its intolerable and he just looked helpless, speechless and shook his head.

Looks to me that it's a normal occurrence there looking at the negative reviews on customer service or lack of. I would give it a -ve review if the feature is available. Disgusting. Uncalled for rudeness. Ruined my day.  I am fuming. Avoid at all cost unless you thrive of rude service and insults.

Despite that, as the teh tarik was already made and I do not want to waste food, I paid  for it ($1.20) and walked away after telling this chap to just chill. He may be having a bad day but he has NO RIGHT to dump it on anyone else.

I won't be giving this shop anymore of my hard earned money. Adios.

Disappointing experience.
Only allowed to order egg prata to maximise earning. Waited for 30mins before some of the food came but they left out the curry for some.  Half of the party didn’t even get to eat at all.
Should have told us earlier if they are attending to huge take away order. But they decided to take our orders and left us hanging.

reviews.text: Must try their bakes if you're a fan of pastries. Highly recommend their almond croissant and dark chocolate sea salt sablé! Be sure to come early as their hot items sell out fast, especially during the weekends.
Always amazing bakes and improving over the years. Keep it up! This is the only long queue I am willing to spend my time queueing.

Maybe its cos I went later in the afternoon... but i felt like comparatively, to other similar places, the pastry seems just a slight tad thicker and less crispy.
Nonetheless, it was pretty good still just that its not exactly a place I would drive 30mins down for just to eat.

The long queue says it all... 5 stars!
My all time favorite bakery. I wish they bring back the toastie with the chili jam though. That was my absolute favorite!

Omg! Pastry and bread heaven! Amazingly delicious bread and coffee! I ate my baguette just as it is, it was lovely!

Queue gets pretty long so do go before they open to queue up and get your bread!

reviews.text: Food is good. The service though could be a little faster. Also it is a halal restaurant so no wine as well. Just something to be aware of. Great place otherwise. Thoroughly enjoyed our dinner

We came here for late lunch on a cool Saturday afternoon treated by lovely daughter. We were not able to do advance booking and tried our luck to walk in and got a table. The staff was kind & friendly.

The place was cosy and clean. The staff who took our order was friendly & swift. The order does not take long to come. The food was delicious!! Best ever Italian pizza ever. The rest of the food was big in portion..definitely will come back again

i don't know why this place has such bad reviews, did i go at the right time, right day? i went to the restaurant yesterday, at around 3pm. the food was really good and portions were decent. the moment they were served i told myself, i will come back here again. my experience there was also very pleasant as staff were really friendly and the food was served fast.

Surprisingly good both service and food. Love the pizza chicken which comes in three level of spiciness. The risotto was a pleasantly good. Caesar salad was a little too citrus and lack the creaminess  the squid ink spaghetti was normal lacks the authenticity taste.
Overall I will still recommend this place for causal dining
Been here 4 times and 1 take away, never disappointed. Tried different food at each visit and all tastes good.

data.body: This humble Muslim-run bakery specialises in decadent, halal-certified sliced cakes, kuehs and cupcakes.

reviews.text:
Ordered an Ondeh cake for a friend's birthday as it is one of his favourite. My first and last time ordering..!! The cake did not come with a message. The delivery was late for at least 2 hours! The assigned driver cancelled the pickup and was not replaced until I enquired on my order status with the platform service provider. Then, found out that the new assigned driver had to make other delivery stops and arrived even much later!

When called up Julie Bakes, the shop assistant alluded that it is not their issue to resolve and did not call me back even as they said they'll check with the delivery team...

Julie Bakes should seriously consider changing its delivery platform service provider. It really puts a dent in the whole experience, including the enjoyment of the cake. Will not order again.👎👎👎 (PS: it should be given ZERO star but there was no such option 😝)

Very pretty cakes. Very responsive seller and prompt actions too. Payment is easy and swift. Delivery is on time and prompt. I ask if they can write something and they also written it. As I gave it to elderly, the word was so big!! Perfect for the receiver.  I didn't get to taste the cake but the receiver love it. Great service and Bakes! Thank you!
Walked in on a whim, very friendly people! Tried the Onde Onde cake, it was delicious! Recommended!

We hired Julie to bake cupcakes and a small wedding cake for our wedding this year- she was so great and easy to work with, and she makes DELICIOUS desserts. Many of our wedding guests raved about her cupcakes and everything was eaten that night!! (Our wedding planner went out of her way to save us a few thankfully!).

Julie also went out of her way to meet with my husband and I for a last-minute cake tasting several months ago. She baked amazing mini cakes for us and provided us with so many flavors and styles to choose from. I couldn’t recommend her enough!!
Has probably the best Ondeh-Ondeh cake I’ve ever had.

Service and cleanliness is also great.

the signature chicken bowl is so tender and delicious.

data.body:
An authentic wagyu beef experience awaits at WakuWaku Yakiniku. Specialising in Japanese Yakiniku BBQ, this Muslim-owned restaurant is Singapore’s first halal yakiniku and they even have a Japanese chef on board to deliver the same dining experience from his home country!

If you’re dining with your loved ones, order one of their famous beef platters that consist of different cuts of meats. You’ll also be pleased to know that they serve jo-karubi (boneless short rib) that is one of the most popular wagyu cuts. For foodies who are feeling adventurous, try the special delicacy called Gyutan, a Japanese dish that’s made from grilled beef tongue.

reviews.text: A nice place to enjoy some Halal Yakiniku. We went during the 2-diners rules implementation during dinner time and we didn't had to wait long even (when we expected to wait to be seated). Nice ambience, food is good (value for money and worth it), nice staffs. Highly recommended if you want to enjoy meat and japanese food.

The BBQ beef was extremely good. Went with my wife, ordered 3 different plates of beef and a bowl of chicken cutlet rice. I have been telling my friends of their beef. Its a must try, at least once in your lifetime.

Ordered the 700g platter and it was superb 👌🏻. Especially with the different meat parts and cuts. Can't get enough of their kimchi too. It wasn't very pickled tasting but tasted very fresh and very well made. Definitely heading back for more 🙌🏻

Very very awesome experience. The quality of beef is quite good and the price is also reasonable. And we liked the fact the staffs made an effort to be more personal by remembering our names. The service provided is also excellent. Highlu recommended!
Meat quality was superb. Service was top notch! They gave great recommendations and taught us the best way to eat yakiniku. Thanks Jamie and everyone of the crew! We'll be back for sure.

data.description: WakuWaku Yakiniku is a Muslim-owned restaurant that serves Japanese yakiniku BBQ. With a Japanese chef on board, feast on delicacies like beef tongue, jo-karubi (boneless short rib), grilled teriyaki salmon, and more.
data.name: WakuWaku Yakiniku

data.body:
Burgers will always have a special place in our hearts, and the same can be said with Fatpapas, a Muslim-owned restaurant that serves up delicious burgers, ribs and shakes. Founded by Bernie and Haikel, they were inspired to create a halal version of Fat Boys, their sister company with a build-your-own-burger menu, and today, Muslim diners can enjoy the same yummy burger too!

Their specialty homemade burgers are made using Chilled Australian chuck tender, and you can taste them in burgers like Shroom Melt, Black Peppercorn Burger, and more. Otherwise, you can enjoy finger-lickin main courses such as BBQ Beef Ribs and Country Fried Steak. Don’t forget to try their Ten Dollar Milkshakes with flavours like chocolate, strawberry, and vanilla.
